62
00:07:06,540 --> 00:07:09,070
Right now? Eleven pm.

63
00:07:09,070 --> 00:07:12,810
What time is our curfew? Eight pm, right?

64
00:07:12,810 --> 00:07:15,710
You told me not to come back if
I was going to break the curfew.

65
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:21,950
That applies only to free-loaders
that live in my house, not to me.

66
00:07:21,950 --> 00:07:25,790
- Why not? - Because, I'm the house owner.

67
00:07:25,790 --> 00:07:26,960
Is it usually like that here?

68
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:30,160
Yes. Everything is the way the
house owner wants it to be.

69
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:31,560
That's the rule.

70
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:36,370
If you think it's unfair,
buy a house yourself, and live there.

71
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:42,070
I'm so tired.

72
00:07:49,610 --> 00:07:51,580
Gosh, you scared me.

73
00:07:51,580 --> 00:07:55,150
When you glare at me like that,
you look like a ghost. Stop looking!

74
00:07:55,150 --> 00:07:56,620
I'm going to keep looking at you like this.

75
00:07:56,620 --> 00:07:57,360
Why?

76
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:59,120
They're my eyes. Since, I'm the owner,

77
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:01,590
I decide if I want to glare at
you or look at you normally.

78
00:08:01,590 --> 00:08:06,400
This is my rule, to glare at you when
I'm angry but have nothing to say.

79
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:09,100
- So? You're going to keep
looking at me like that?- Yes.

80
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:09,970
Why?

81
00:08:09,970 --> 00:08:12,900
Because I want to look at you to make
up for the time I couldn't look at you.

82
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:22,380
Do as you like. You'll probably be dizzy.

83
00:08:26,590 --> 00:08:28,350
Oh yeah.

84
00:08:31,660 --> 00:08:34,090
Let me ask you something.

85
00:08:34,090 --> 00:08:34,890
What?

86
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:39,460
When you got into that car accident, at the ER...

87
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:40,370
Yes?

88
00:08:40,370 --> 00:08:42,670
You said that you had a dream, right?

89
00:08:42,670 --> 00:08:44,500
Heo Joon Jae.

90
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,540
Are you okay?

91
00:08:46,540 --> 00:08:49,040
I had a dream.

92
00:08:50,080 --> 00:08:53,010
You held my hand.

93
00:08:53,010 --> 00:08:55,410
You rescued me.

94
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:57,420
Yeah, you're right. I did.

95
00:08:57,420 --> 00:08:59,950
What kind of dream?

96
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:06,120
So, in the dream, how did I save you?

97
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:20,810
I mean, there are several ways to save a person.

98
00:09:20,810 --> 00:09:24,140
I could have grabbed you when you
were about to fall off a high place,

99
00:09:24,140 --> 00:09:27,780
or I could have lifted you out of a deep pit.

100
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:30,180
How did I do it?

101
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:33,150
You don't remember? Okay.

102
00:09:33,150 --> 00:09:36,860
Then, what about the time period?
What time period was it?

103
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:41,630
Perhaps, was I wearing old
time traditional clothes?

104
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:42,960
You know what old time traditional
clothes look like, right?

105
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:49,030
You know that drama you like, The Crown
Prince's Woman? Clothes that they wear in that.

106
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:54,110
- The thing is... - Yes?

107
00:09:54,110 --> 00:09:57,780
- The thing is, I don't really remember.

108
00:09:59,340 --> 00:10:03,320
I really can't remember it at all.

109
00:10:04,980 --> 00:10:09,020
Okay. I'm sure that's the case.

110
00:10:09,020 --> 00:10:14,430
You can't even remember your own name.
How would you remember that?

111
00:10:14,430 --> 00:10:16,060
Okay. Go back up.

112
00:10:16,060 --> 00:10:18,760
Okay. Heo Joon Jae, sleep well!

113
00:10:21,870 --> 00:10:25,570
What was that?
She said she would watch me all night.

114
00:10:25,570 --> 00:10:30,540
Thinking about it now, she really doesn't
take responsibility for her words.

115
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:36,010
I feel restless for no reason now.

116
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:40,490
So this is what lying feels like.

117
00:10:40,490 --> 00:10:45,290
It makes my heart pound a
little, but it is convenient.

118
00:10:45,290 --> 00:10:48,890
It's a good thing Heo Joon
Jae cannot hear my real voice.

119
00:11:00,370 --> 00:11:02,570
I'm sorry.

120
00:11:02,570 --> 00:11:04,740
I came too late.

121
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:19,730
What are you doing?

122
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:22,530
Why are you coming out in the middle of sleeping?

123
00:11:23,460 --> 00:11:25,600
Give me one too.

124
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,970
I'm really a little strange these days.

125
00:11:29,970 --> 00:11:32,640
Why? Did you dream about
being Kim Dam Ryeong again?

126
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:34,710
No.

127
00:11:38,210 --> 00:11:39,440
Joon Jae.

128
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:43,920
Do you know what you have to find the strangest?

129
00:11:43,920 --> 00:11:45,680
- What?  - Cheong.

130
00:11:46,690 --> 00:11:48,750
Don't you find Cheong strange?

131
00:11:51,390 --> 00:11:54,290
She's naturally a little strange.

132
00:11:54,290 --> 00:11:58,260
Again, don't try to just
gloss over it like that again.

133
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:03,440
Fine, Cheong is pretty and sweet-hearted.

134
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:06,410
She really seems as if she's
from an entirely different world,

135
00:12:06,410 --> 00:12:09,270
but she's strange.

136
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:12,500
Truthfully, last time, when we went to
the hospital I asked for Cheong's X-ray films

137
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:16,480
and showed them to a doctor hyung I know.

138
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,280
Why did you do something like that?!

139
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:23,160
Don't get all worked up and just listen. They said
the films got switched but I didn't think so.

140
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:25,730
If you were your normal self,
you would have been suspicious too,

141
00:12:25,730 --> 00:12:27,930
but you seem to be losing your
wits when it comes to Cheong these days.

142
00:12:27,930 --> 00:12:29,290
And?

143
00:12:29,290 --> 00:12:30,800
He says the films weren't switched?

144
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:33,100
He says that the films are
definitely of one person.

145
00:12:34,130 --> 00:12:36,740
A broken bone that may not have
even fused after six weeks,

146
00:12:36,740 --> 00:12:40,870
reattached after not even a week, and she
was perfectly sprightly even after that.

147
00:12:40,870 --> 00:12:42,340
Isn't it strange?

148
00:12:43,180 --> 00:12:45,380
And this.

149
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:55,490
A kid that has no job or skills here

150
00:12:55,490 --> 00:12:57,420
keeps this kind of thing in a plastic
bag, this much worth,

151
00:12:57,420 --> 00:13:00,230
saying she'll sell all of them and give it to you.

152
00:13:01,330 --> 00:13:02,960
Where did she get this?

153
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,000
That's what I don't know.

154
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:11,170
And also, it's certain that
you met Cheong in Spain,

155
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:14,040
but you still can't remember it all this time.

156
00:13:19,780 --> 00:13:22,450
Why do you think that is?

157
00:13:22,450 --> 00:13:25,480
You said that was why you were
letting Cheong live in this house.

158
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:28,150
You must not even be curious
about that anymore, huh?

159
00:13:28,150 --> 00:13:31,320
Then what about you, Hyung?
Why are you curious about that?

160
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:36,330
Me? I'm afraid that you'll
become a good guy, Joon Jae.

161
00:13:36,330 --> 00:13:39,700
I've barely made you a bad guy
and now you're finally useful.

162
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:43,900
After meeting Cheong, you seem to want to become
a good guy, so it's giving me cause for concern.

163
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:47,170
If you become a good guy, you'll leave me.

164
00:13:47,170 --> 00:13:50,240
You're saying all kinds of useless things.

165
00:13:50,240 --> 00:13:53,510
I'm curious as to what kind of kid
she is too. It's interesting, right?

166
00:13:53,510 --> 00:13:56,980
I'm going to make sure to find out. Oh, I've got to pee.

167
00:14:00,550 --> 00:14:05,920
I think I've got to be the first to
find out what kind of kid you are.

168
00:14:11,260 --> 00:14:13,500
Squad Chief, look at this.

169
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:16,470
What is it?

170
00:14:16,470 --> 00:14:18,700
I looked through Ma Dae Young's
previous convictions records again.

171
00:14:18,700 --> 00:14:19,600
I told you to catch him.

