00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:22,410
Why were you looking through
his previous conviction records again?

173
00:14:22,410 --> 00:14:26,040
He's got 13 previous convictions
mostly for violence. Why?

174
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:29,210
Because he has an anger management control
defect. But there's something that's strange.

175
00:14:29,210 --> 00:14:30,120
What?

176
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:35,850
From '88-'89, in the space of that one year,
he committed over thirty cases of burglary.

177
00:14:35,850 --> 00:14:38,420
And at a department store in Seongnam,

178
00:14:38,420 --> 00:14:40,430
in a mart shopping mall.

179
00:14:41,260 --> 00:14:43,660
Ma Dae Young Record  Serious Crime Squad

180
00:14:43,660 --> 00:14:45,000
Why?

181
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:49,270
During this time,

182
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,070
he had a woman.

183
00:15:02,450 --> 00:15:04,050
Are you okay, Father?

184
00:15:04,050 --> 00:15:08,020
It's because I keep getting a little dizzy.

185
00:15:08,020 --> 00:15:12,160
Honey, make sure to take your
medicine well after eating your meal.

186
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:14,290
It's really a concern.

187
00:15:14,290 --> 00:15:16,830
It keeps getting worse.

188
00:15:16,830 --> 00:15:20,500
Honey, don't go to work
today and stay home and rest.

189
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:23,140
If there's something important, tell me.

190
00:15:23,140 --> 00:15:26,340
I'll relay it to Secretary Kim.

191
00:15:30,980 --> 00:15:32,680
Have some, Father.

192
00:15:43,820 --> 00:15:48,290
Yu Na. You have a make-up class at Korean
hakwon (after school academy). Don't be late.

193
00:16:03,910 --> 00:16:07,250
What are you going to do if
you get the pink octopus?

194
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:10,380
- Oh, hi. - Hi.

195
00:16:10,380 --> 00:16:12,250
But how did you know about this place?

196
00:16:12,250 --> 00:16:18,160
I didn't go to school today, but upon not going
to school, I suddenly had no place to go.

197
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:22,590
I remembered you said you lived in this
neighborhood before, so I tried coming this way.

198
00:16:22,590 --> 00:16:26,930
But how did you know that I thought that I had
to pull out the pink octopus no matter what?

199
00:16:26,930 --> 00:16:29,270
I knew since you said it.

200
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:34,170
When I was coming up behind, you kept saying
that you wanted to make sure to pull that one.

201
00:16:34,170 --> 00:16:35,940
I didn't.

202
00:16:35,940 --> 00:16:38,240
That wasn't a voice you could hear.

203
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:41,810
Well anyway, I heard.

204
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:44,480
Watch.

205
00:16:48,190 --> 00:16:50,390
I got it, right?

206
00:16:50,390 --> 00:16:52,220
Hey, Sim Cheong.

207
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:59,160
Where did she go again?

208
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:01,930
Anyhow, she gets around well.

209
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:12,480
Really.

210
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:15,480
Where did she get all of these?

211
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:19,180
But why is she saying that she'll
make money and give it all to me?

212
00:17:19,180 --> 00:17:23,060
When did I ask her for money? What is it?

213
00:17:23,060 --> 00:17:27,190
Oh yes. Oh Baek's mother. You called again.

214
00:17:27,190 --> 00:17:29,930
Of course. I did speak to him.

215
00:17:29,930 --> 00:17:33,160
It's not easy to schedule
appointments with our president.

216
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:35,630
He's originally such a busy individual.

217
00:17:35,630 --> 00:17:40,910
Yes, I'll try to speak to him further about it
but please don't have any big expectations.

218
00:17:40,910 --> 00:17:44,410
Aigoo, yes, yes. Yes.

219
00:17:44,410 --> 00:17:47,710
Hey, this ahjumma is really hyped up.

220
00:17:48,610 --> 00:17:51,380
Why are you so hyper now?

221
00:17:51,380 --> 00:17:54,620
Are you looking for someone? Cheong?

222
00:17:54,620 --> 00:17:56,720
No. Where's Tae Oh?

223
00:17:57,720 --> 00:18:01,560
Are you really a con artist?
Why are you so bad at lying?

224
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:07,570
Hey, did I tell you to charge
your cell phone or not?

225
00:18:07,570 --> 00:18:12,370
Why do you carry it around turned off?
Is it a decoration? Is it a weapon?

226
00:18:12,370 --> 00:18:15,010
- It's dead.  - It's not dead, but it's turned off.

227
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:19,240
Give it some food. You don't miss out on
one meal for yourself and eat so well,

228
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:21,710
but don't you get the idea that he might be hungry?

229
00:18:21,710 --> 00:18:25,120
The phone gets discharged.
It's not that it's hungry.

230
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:28,290
- What are you about?  - She's my friend.

231
00:18:30,320 --> 00:18:31,860
Let's go inside.

232
00:18:33,330 --> 00:18:35,120
Why are all your friends like that?

233
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:38,330
Last time it was a beggar,
this time it's an elementary schooler?

234
00:18:38,330 --> 00:18:40,100
Ahjussi, (you're one to talk), you're unemployed.

235
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:43,740
Who is an ahjussi and who is a bum?
You're wrong on both counts.

236
00:18:43,740 --> 00:18:47,340
At a time when others are going to
work, if you're lazing about the house,

237
00:18:47,340 --> 00:18:51,640
lying down and watching TV, or playing
games, it says you are unemployed.

238
00:18:53,610 --> 00:18:56,620
- Heo Joon Jae, you're unemployed?
- I'm not unemployed.

239
00:18:57,620 --> 00:19:01,420
I'm... a freelancer.

240
00:19:01,420 --> 00:19:03,920
It's a specialized job so I can work from home.

241
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:04,840
That's true.

242
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:08,890
Heo Joon Jae is a person who works for the
country more diligently than a civil servant.

243
00:19:08,890 --> 00:19:14,530
He redistributes wealth also. So when you grow
up later you have to become like Heo Joon Jae.

244
00:19:14,530 --> 00:19:16,170
